Status;
	runs on Sun4 under SunOS 4.x (Solaris 1.x)

		I used assembler to create the data segment.  It may
		be as simple as supplying a new stgasm.h to bring it
		up on another CPU, providing the local assembler allows
		arithmetic on relocatable symbols.

		libunix may use many Sun specific library routines,
		I haven't paid much attention to portability. The library
		should be split up into system-independant functions
		and system-specific versions of system-dependant functions!

	May run VERY slowly;

		genc.sno itself runs "only" 10x slower than under
		Catspaw SPARC (Macro) SPITBOL.  This is quite respectable.

		However programs which make extensive use of matching
		may run much slower.

		The pattern scanner and some pattern matching routines
		get split up into many small, mutually recusrsive
		routines!!

		gcc inlining may resolve this

	LOAD() is implemented on SunOS4!!
		see DOC/LOAD.doc

I/O;

	named files can be opened by supplying an optional fourth
	argument to INPUT() and OUTPUT(), like in Catspaw SNOBOL4.

	input is padded with spaces out to the default record length (80).
	&TRIM defaults to 1, so any trailing spaces are lost on input.

	by default INPUT is attached to unit 5, and standard input.
	by default OUTPUT is attached to unit 6, and standard output.
	by default PUNCH is attached to unit 7, and standard error!!!

Command line args;

	snobol4 [ options ... ] [ files ... ]

	-d NNN
		Have dynamic region contain space for NNN descriptors
		default is 25000.

	-k
		Run programs with compilation errors

	-l
		Reenable listing to OUTPUT. default is -UNLIST

	-r
		Continue reading INPUT from input file(s) after END
		label.  otherwise INPUT defaults (back) to stdin after
		compilation.

To build;

	cd lib
	make
	cd ..
	make

The tar file contains a binary of snobol4 for Sun4 / OS 4.x.  IT
SHOULD NOT BE NEEDED (unless you touch the source files) As all
generated files are provided.  The generated files are NOT system
dependant!!!

